abstract: Clever and vaguely profound, aphorisms should be the ideal expression for our distracted moment.
snippet: Clever and vaguely profound, aphorisms should be the ideal expression for our distracted moment.
lead_paragraph: This should be the golden age of the aphorism. Constrained as we all are by time, attention and social media platform character limits, when we pull out our smartphones and stare into their illuminated fields, we can take in only so much. Shouldn’t those words be perfectly chosen to vibrate with hidden meanings?

abstract: While fighting for stricter gun laws, I was always told I didn’t understand. Maybe now I do.
snippet: While fighting for stricter gun laws, I was always told I didn’t understand. Maybe now I do.
lead_paragraph: To be clear, there was nothing I could’ve done to save him. It’s just a fantasy that has been circling my brain in a holding pattern for decades — that somehow I could have intervened.

abstract: A case would renew scrutiny of the company amid a growing chorus of criticism about the power of big tech.
snippet: A case would renew scrutiny of the company amid a growing chorus of criticism about the power of big tech.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Justice Department is exploring whether to open a case against Google for potential antitrust violations, putting renewed scrutiny on the company amid a growing chorus of criticism about the power of Big Tech, three people with knowledge of the deliberations said Friday.

abstract: The tech cold war is heating up. U.S. companies that depend on the giant China market are preparing themselves for the fallout.
snippet: The tech cold war is heating up. U.S. companies that depend on the giant China market are preparing themselves for the fallout.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — When Silicon Valley looks west to China, it sees many things. More than a billion hungry consumers. A cheap source of labor. A competitor, partner, supplier and security risk.

headline_main: The Woman Behind the Creature From the Black Lagoon

abstract: The AMC horror series is one of several adaptations the best-selling horror author (and son of Stephen King) has in the works, after multiple stalled attempts.
snippet: The AMC horror series is one of several adaptations the best-selling horror author (and son of Stephen King) has in the works, after multiple stalled attempts.
lead_paragraph: On a sunny spring morning in a hotel near Central Park, the writer Joe Hill settled into an overstuffed chair before an 18th-century-style fireplace, received tea and sandwiches — rectangular, crusts removed — and stroked his graying beard. He was there to talk about a vile old man with rotten teeth who feasts on the souls of young children.
